  • Variable label: Number of cigarettes smoked per week
  • Variable description: Number of cigarettes smoked per week. Current smokers cigarettes only
  • Domain: Lifestyle and health behaviours

2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute n_cigarettes from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • heskb*5+heskc*2
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996

R script:

ELSA_ds_w1 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w1$id)
# All individuals have the same missing values for both variables.
ELSA_ds_w1$n_cigarettes <- car::recode((ELSA_w1$heskb * 5 + ELSA_w1$heskc * 
    2), "-1*7 = 996;-8*7 = 998;-9*7 = 997 ")

2.1.2.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute n_cigarettes from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • HeSkb*5+HeSkc*2
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996

R script:

ELSA_ds_w2 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w2$id)
# All individuals have the same missing values for both variables, but there
# is an individual whose answer to HeSkb is 13 and that has missing value -8
# in HeSkc.
ELSA_ds_w2$n_cigarettes <- car::recode((ELSA_w2$HeSkb * 5 + ELSA_w2$HeSkc * 
    2), "-1*7 = 996;-8*7 = 998;-9*7 = 997 ")
ELSA_ds_w2$n_cigarettes[which(ELSA_w2$HeSkc == -8)] <- 998

2.1.7.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute n_cigarettes from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • HeSkb*5+HeSkc*2
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996

R script:

ELSA_ds_w7 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w7$id)
# All individuals have the same missing values for both variables, but there
# is an individual whose answer to HeSkb is 0 and that has missing value -8
# in HeSkc, and another whose answer to HeSkc is 10 and that has missing
# value -8 in HeSkb
ELSA_ds_w7$n_cigarettes <- car::recode((ELSA_w7$HeSkb * 5 + ELSA_w7$HeSkc * 
    2), "-1*7 = 996;-8*7 = 998;-9*7 = 997 ; -8*2 = 998")
ELSA_ds_w7$n_cigarettes[which(ELSA_w7$HeSkb == -8)] <- 998
